- Guess who asked me out.

05:45.779 --> 05:47.440
- Who?
- David O'Dooley.

05:47.581 --> 05:48.570
Oh.

05:48.715 --> 05:49.876
He's a senior,

05:50.016 --> 05:52.007
and, uh, he's an editor
for the high school paper.

05:52.152 --> 05:53.551
He's such a hunk.

05:53.687 --> 05:54.813
Oh.

05:54.955 --> 05:56.354
Yeah, well,
that's-that's terrific.

05:56.489 --> 05:57.855
He's got a car and everything.

05:57.991 --> 05:59.220
- A car?
- Yeah.

05:59.359 --> 06:01.123
This is going to be a car date?

06:01.261 --> 06:02.387
Well, I don't know.

06:02.529 --> 06:03.928
Dad's not going
to be thrilled about that.

06:04.064 --> 06:05.588
- You know how protective he is.
- Oh.

06:05.732 --> 06:08.292
He's no problem.
<i>l-I'll</i> think of something.

06:10.270 --> 06:12.466
HOWARD:
You what?!

06:12.606 --> 06:14.597
Definitely not!

06:14.741 --> 06:16.141
You are too young to car-date.

06:16.276 --> 06:18.642
But Richie was younger than me
when you let him go.

06:18.778 --> 06:20.644
Tell him, Mom.
Get up and tell him.

06:20.780 --> 06:23.978
Oh... yes, he was younger.

06:26.086 --> 06:27.644
Well, they've
got you there, Dad.

06:27.787 --> 06:28.846
Well, that's different.

06:28.989 --> 06:31.014
