you know, spoon.

07:19.539 --> 07:21.530
You were a hunk.

07:23.076 --> 07:24.635
Well, you two talk this out.

07:24.778 --> 07:27.178
I got to cram for an exam.

07:27.314 --> 07:29.009
This isn't fair.

07:29.149 --> 07:31.345
I mean, you let Richie go,
but you won't let me.

07:31.484 --> 07:34.078
Now, when I was 14,
you said I was too young.

07:34.220 --> 07:36.712
When I was a freshman, you said,
"Wait until next year."

07:36.856 --> 07:40.258
Well, it's next year,
and you still won't let me go.

07:40.393 --> 07:42.589
Dad, don't you trust me?

07:42.729 --> 07:45.255
Of course I trust you.

07:45.398 --> 07:46.866
Okay, you can go.

07:47.000 --> 07:49.093
But I want to meet
this young man first.

07:49.235 --> 07:50.328
Is that fair enough?

07:50.470 --> 07:51.869
- Yeah, you can meet him.
- Okay.

07:52.005 --> 07:54.497
Thanks, Dad. Oh, wait until
Jenny Piccalo hears about this.

07:56.042 --> 07:58.136
<i>No, I don't know
where we're going, Jenny.</i>

