I was so excited,
I forgot to ask.

08:00.280 --> 08:01.645
-(doorbell rings)
- Oh, my gosh.

08:01.781 --> 08:04.182
Oh, oh, uh, he's here.
I got to hang up. Bye.

08:04.317 --> 08:05.512
Mom, Mom, he's here.
He's here. He's here.

08:05.652 --> 08:07.279
- Oh, oh, I'm so excited.
- Oh, no. Wait. Here. Here.

08:07.420 --> 08:09.753
- Now, don't... don't act
so excited. -Okay.

08:09.889 --> 08:11.118
Try to be a young lady.

08:11.257 --> 08:13.249
Okay.

08:18.765 --> 08:21.928
Oh, well...

08:22.068 --> 08:23.968
Hello, Chachi.

08:24.104 --> 08:27.130
It's always nice
to see that smile of yours.

08:27.273 --> 08:29.333
Hi, Mrs. C. Here's
the prune pitter you ordered.

08:29.476 --> 08:31.103
The prunes will be here
next week.

08:31.244 --> 08:32.506
Oh, thank you.

08:32.645 --> 08:34.773
Oh, yeah, the holiday season
is coming up.

08:34.914 --> 08:37.440
And this prune pitter
makes the perfect gift.

08:37.583 --> 08:40.610
Oh, I already have a gift
for Howard.

08:40.754 --> 08:46.192
Well... maybe Mother Kelp
could use a couple of these.

08:48.928 --> 08:50.920
Wah, wah, wah.

08:51.064 --> 08:54.591
Thank you. I feel kind of...
wah, wah, wah.

08:54.734 --> 08:56.361
I've got a big date.

08:56.503 --> 08:58.664
Oh, yeah? Who is he?

08:58.805 --> 09:01.467
His name is David O'Dooley.

09:01.608 --> 09:04.236
That wimp?

09:04.377 --> 09:06.368
What does he got
that I haven't got?

09:06.513 --> 09:10.210
Well, he's older, he's taller,
he's a senior, and he has a car.

09:10.350 --> 09:11.408
Besides that.

09:11.551 --> 09:13.485
Come on, Chachi.

09:13.620 --> 09:15.588
I'll give you some milk
and crackers.

09:15.722 --> 09:18.748
I would give you some rye bread,
but Richard forgot it.

09:18.892 --> 09:21.884
(Richie humming)

09:26.699 --> 09:28.964
Party time. (laughs)

09:29.102 --> 09:31.093
Hey. Hi, Joanie.

09:31.237 --> 09:32.671
-(laughter)
- Uh,

09:32.806 --> 09:34.831
well, I-I'm doubling
with Fonz tonight.

09:34.974 --> 09:36.636
He's taking Blossom.

09:36.776 --> 09:38.005
Only one girl?

09:38.144 --> 09:39.510
Must be a slow night.

09:39.646 --> 09:41.978
Hey, that's great.

09:42.115 --> 09:43.514
Drink your milk.

09:43.650 --> 09:45.914
All right, let's get this show
on the road.

09:46.052 --> 09:47.349
Hi, Fonz.

09:47.487 --> 09:52.118
Hey, Joanie, how come
you look so... so tonight, huh?

09:52.258 --> 09:54.454
Well, it's my first real date...

09:54.594 --> 09:56.460
in a car... and everything.

09:56.596 --> 09:58.462
All right, hold it!

09:58.598 --> 10:01.226
Did you say car date?

10:01.367 --> 10:02.767
Are you old enough?

10:02.902 --> 10:04.871
Look, uh, there are some tricks
of the trade

10:05.004 --> 10:06.404
you got to know, see, and, uh,

10:06.539 --> 10:08.269
I'm going to give them to you
right now.

10:08.408 --> 10:10.433
